message: Hello! I found that combining only two items, especially those with similar features (e.g., natural+soft or artificial+hard), often yields a neutral item. Applying the 'frame' tool to these 2-item composites seems to be the best way to get positive values (e.g., 20). Combining three or more items almost always results in an 'overcomplicated' item with a highly negative value. If you get an 'overcomplicated' item, 'scissors' might improve its value, but using tools on an item multiple times can drastically reduce its value. Focus on getting a 2-item combo then framing it. Good luck!
